title: London-bound flight is intercepted by two German fighters | Daily Mail Online
text: Two German fighter jets intercepted a London-bound airliner after air traffic control failed to establish contact with its pilot. The Euro Fighters were scrambled last Thursday as the Jet Airways Boeing 777 was crossing over Cologne. Footage captured from a British Airways plane trailing behind shows the fighters flying alongside the Indian passenger jet high above the clouds. Footage captured from a British Airways plane trailing behind shows the fighters flying alongside the Indian passenger jet high above the clouds The fighters soon managed to establish contact with the Jet Airways plane, which had set off from Mumbai, and soon returned to base. But that is not the end of the story, if some online commenters are to be believed. They have pointed out that at around one minute and 30 seconds into the video you can see a small dark object moving faster than the other aeroplanes. RELATED ARTICLES
